  data.steps.forEach(step => {
    outputCard(
      `Step ${step.number}: ${step.heading}`,
      step.text
    );
  });

  outputQuickReplies([
    { label: "U.S. 988 Lifeline", url: "tel:988" },
    { label: "findahelpline.com", url: "https://findahelpline.com" },
    { label: "Local Emergency (911)", url: "tel:911" }
  ]);

  outputCard(
    "Resources",
    `Canada 988 | U.K. 116 123 | Australia 13 11 14 | NZ 0800 543 354 (HELP)`
  );

  outputCard("Note", data.meta.footer);
}
```

**Implementation notes**
- `outputCard()` would display text blocks or speech bubbles in your interface.  
- `outputQuickReplies()` turns hotline links into tappable buttons.  
- Always include a persistent emergency option (e.g., “Call 911”) visible at all times.  
- Never delay or replace professional crisis support — every button leads directly to verified resources.  

This structure keeps the bot’s tone compassionate and directs users only toward **immediate safety and help**—exactly what you want in a wellbeing or moderation context, with no content that could be read as endorsing or validating self‑harm.
